# Next.js 16 + React 19 Patterns

> ⚠️ Next.js 16 has breaking API changes. Always read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before using any Next.js API.

## Component Pattern

All components are Client Components. Structure:

```tsx
"use client";

import { motion, useInView } from "framer-motion";
import { useRef } from "react";
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

export default function SectionName() {
  const ref = useRef(null);
  const isInView = useInView(ref, { once: true, margin: "-100px" });

  return (
    <section ref={ref} id="section-id" className="relative py-24 sm:py-32">
      {/* content */}
    </section>
  );
}
```

## Framer Motion

Use `useInView` + `motion` for scroll-triggered animations. Always set `once: true` to avoid re-triggering:

```tsx
const variants = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0, y: 30 },
  visible: { opacity: 1, y: 0, transition: { duration: 0.6 } },
};

<motion.div
  variants={variants}
  initial="hidden"
  animate={isInView ? "visible" : "hidden"}
/>
```

## Zustand State

Access global state via `use-store.ts`:

```tsx
import { useStore } from "@/store/use-store";
const { mobileMenuOpen, setMobileMenuOpen } = useStore();
```

Do not create additional stores — extend the existing one.

## Section ID Convention

Navigation anchors require matching `id` attributes:

| Nav link | Required `id` |
|----------|--------------|
| `#services` | `id="services"` |
| `#case-studies` | `id="case-studies"` |
| `#deployments` | `id="deployments"` |
| `#testimonials` | `id="testimonials"` |
| `#pricing` | `id="pricing"` |
| `#faq` | `id="faq"` |

## Import Paths

Use path alias `@/` which maps to project root:

```tsx
// ✅
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";
import { useStore } from "@/store/use-store";

// ❌
import { cn } from "../../lib/utils";
```
